### Description

Angular router removes trailing slash from URL - it's not clear in the docs how to disable this behaviour. (As for reasoning why I am looking to do this, 1) Certain sites already following a structure with trailing slashes would need to retain that structure after being upgraded to angular and 2) Certain deployment tools (ex: Cloudflare pages) force trailing slashes on all URLs).

Navigating to a prerendered URL, ex: /blog/ is fine - but once the bundle is loaded it changes the browser location to /blog.

Attempting to resolve this using a custom url serializer works - but it breaks routerLinkActive.

```
export class TrailingSlashUrlSerializer extends DefaultUrlSerializer {
  private static _withTrailingSlash(url: string): string {
    const splitOn = url.indexOf('?') > - 1 ? '?' : '#';
    const pathArr = url.split(splitOn);

    if (!pathArr[0].endsWith('/')) {
      let fileName: string = url.substring( url.lastIndexOf('/') + 1);
      if (fileName.indexOf('.') === -1) {
        pathArr[0] += '/';
      }
    }
    const result = pathArr.join(splitOn);

    return result;
  }

  serialize(tree: UrlTree): string {
    return TrailingSlashUrlSerializer._withTrailingSlash(super.serialize(tree));
  }
}

```

